Package co.cookies.sdk

Interface SDKConfiguration

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CookiesSDKManager, ExtensibleCookiesSDK
    public interface SDKConfiguration
    Defines the API surface for the main collection of configurable components that compose together to enable gRPC services hosted by Cookies.

    To customize low-level access to service interfaces, acquire your services with a customized implementation of this interface. CookiesSDKManager is the default implementation.

    For example, to acquire an instance of the CatalogClientV1 with custom configuration: CatalogClient.configure(new SDKConfiguration() { // ... your implementation here });
